The show's existence is not in dispute. Its omission from the canonical record is not in dispute. The interpretation of that omission as a structural decision rather than an oversight — because Lucy McKenzie's presence as herself on the same walls where the first Banksy publication was launched makes the show's inclusion in the official record incompatible with the maintenance of the Banksy identity — is the analytical argument of this article.

